- <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                xml:id="ttag1"
                ref="#misc_854"
                type="miscellaneous">
               <term xml:id="tag1">
          It has often happened during<lb/>the progress of Science
        </term>
            </rs> that two<lb/>
doctrines immediately opposite have<lb/>
been supported with great powers of<lb/>
reasoning &amp; almost with equal plausibility.<lb/>
Such a circumstance however<lb/>
almost always marks with the infancy<lb/>
of the study &amp; the imperfection<lb/>
of the methods of investigation.<lb/>
It proves that speculation merely<lb/>
has been employed or partial<lb/>
facts only examined: And the<lb/>
Philosophical enquirer in opposing<lb/>
supposition to supposition &amp; error<lb/>
to error will instantly perceive<lb/>
            <unclear xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"/>
            <lb/>
            <lb/>
            <pb xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                n="4"
                xml:id="pb-4"
                facs="#i4"/>
            <lb/>
the insufficiency of either class of<lb/>
opinions; &amp; will thus preserve<lb/>
the mind free from doubt, from<lb/>
the prejudice of false systems,<lb/>
&amp; from mistake &amp; confusion.<lb/>
- This method may be <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">often</del>
            <add xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0">sometimes</add>
            <lb/>
applied with great success in<lb/>
the examination of Geological<lb/>
theories. - It <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">sometimes</del> removes the<lb/>
necessity of strict discussion &amp;<lb/>
it often devellopes absurdity without<lb/>
the assistance of laborious logical<lb/>
deductions.<lb/>
